With respect to Date primitives,there are a couple of ways we could store these: ISO 8601 strings or a int64 of millis since the unix epoch (akin to Java Date values), plus a timezone adjustment.  E.g.: 
```
message Date {
    int64 milliseconds = 1;
    int16 timezone_offset = 2; // offset in minutes
}
```
The default timezone offset would be `0`, and therefore be `Z`

